      <hedline>
        <hl1>Switch It Off</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Jan Owens letter on Betsy Wade's June 4 column on avoiding noise while traveling suggests chcking to see if sporting events are being hosted by nearby schools and universities (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor: I appreciate Betsy Wade's comments on avoiding noise while traveling. May I also suggest checking to see if there are sporting events being hosted by nearby schools and universities.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor: I appreciate Betsy Wade's comments on avoiding noise while traveling. May I also suggest checking to see if there are sporting events being hosted by nearby schools and universities.</p>
        <p>Last year, our vacation in southern Rhode Island around the Fourth of July was a game of avoiding girls' soccer (or volleyball?) teams invading the local restaurants, the result of a tournament. While their table manners were generally good, the  long tables of loud young ladies  raised the decibel level in the restaurants into the ''rowdy'' zone.</p>
        <p>JAN OWENS  Racine, Wis.</p>
      </block>
